## Testing plan

Gates (always all three): `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `constructor-unit-tests` gate runs the new `OpticalConstructor.Tests` files; must pass and increase the count over the prior slice's baseline.
- AC-J1 (`SchematicGeometryTests.fs`, schematic portion): the pure band-height function is monotonic in `Thickness` meters; `Thickness.Infinity` draws as the fixed-height semi-infinite band; `Substrate.Wedge` draws with a sloped lower edge (geometry verified without an Avalonia surface).
- AC-J2 (`RepeatBuilderTests.fs`): `expand cell R` yields exactly N*R `Layer`s in cell order assignable to `OpticalSystem.films`; no new period/super-layer type. `RepeatBuilder.expand` stays the pure `List.replicate count cell |> List.concat` with NO reference to the slice-015 `Validation.fs`; the `R < 1` rejection via the J.9 validator is owned and tested in slice 015's `ValidationTests.fs` (AC-J9), not here.
- AC-J3 (`TemplatesTests.fs`): each of the six templates produces an `OpticalConstructorProject` passing the §A.7 project schema through the schema-validated open path; the DBR template's films equal `RepeatBuilder.expand` output.
- AC-J4: covered by the MVU update path — a drop message replaces `Layer.properties` with the resolved `OpticalProperties` while `Layer.thickness` is unchanged, immutably.
- AC-J5: workspace overlay delegates to `plotComparison` (`Charting.fs:38`) via Part H §H.4 with no Part-J-local overlay implementation.
- `build` gate green at Release/x64; `unit-tests` gate (BerremanTests) stays green (not touched here).

## Risks

- **Medium.** Cross-slice seam discipline is the load-bearing risk: J.2's `R<1` rejection is owned by the slice-015 J.9 validator and `RepeatBuilder.expand` MUST NOT forward-reference `Validation.fs` (a later-slice symbol the one-round-per-slice arc-runner cannot compile), J.3 must route through the slice-003 `openProject` (not a private deserialize), J.4 must resolve through the slice-004 by-id material resolver (not re-resolve dispersion), and J.5 must overlay through the slice-012 `plotComparison` (not a local multi-curve plot). Mitigation: keep `RepeatBuilder.expand` a pure `List.replicate count cell |> List.concat` with no reference to the slice-015 `Validation.fs`, keep the schematic a pure `OpticalSystem -> control` projection provable headless, and assert the delegations by test. Splitting `SchematicGeometryTests.fs` with slice 016 (AC-J12) — keep this slice's additions confined to the AC-J1 cases.

## Hand-off

The first Part J UX tranche exists: the to-scale schematic (`Schematic.fs`), the pure repeat builder (`RepeatBuilder.fs`), the six code-defined templates (`Templates.fs`), and the comparison workspace (`Workspace.fs`), with the AC-J1/AC-J2/AC-J3 tests green. Slice 015 adds the persistent environment/favorites, preferences, theme/dockable panels, and the J.9 `Validation` module through which the repeat builder's `R < 1` rejection is enforced and tested (slice 015's `ValidationTests.fs`, AC-J9) — slice 014's `RepeatBuilder.fs`/`RepeatBuilderTests.fs` carry no reference to it. Slice 016 (LAST) adds the job runner, help/gallery, and the `SystemView3D` viewport — and extends `SchematicGeometryTests.fs` with the AC-J12 portion. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
